# Appendix B â€” Mendix Cloud (Licensed Environments)

Inside Control Center â†’ **Mendix Cloud**, you can see:

### ğŸ”¹ Running Apps
Applications currently deployed and active.

### ğŸ”¹ Not Deployed
Nodes created but without a deployment.

### ğŸ”¹ Private Cloud Apps
Apps associated with your account and deployed on:

- Azure  
- AWS  
- GCP  
- Registered Kubernetes clusters  

### ğŸ”¹ Connected Mode
If the cluster is registered and synchronized:

- CI/CD integration becomes available  
- Logs and metrics are visible  
- Deployments can be controlled from Mendix  

---

# Appendix C â€” Other Cloud Views

### **Cloud (All Apps)**
Shows all applications created by your organization.

### **Other Apps**
Apps deployed outside Mendix Cloud or in private cloud.

### **Deactivated Apps**
Apps removed from the registry or migrated.

---

# Appendix D â€” Health Dashboard

Displays the health of environments.

- Monitors **cluster**, not app  
- Shows:
- Critical errors  
- Node status  
- Availability  

---

# Appendix E â€” People (Users & Permissions)

Here you can see:

